comments.body:
The `production` deployment for this was successful, however there appears to be an error with the NGINX Plus load balancer. Currently this has successfully deployed on the server itself:

```
pulsys@oawaiver-prod1:~$ curl http://localhost

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <meta name="Generator" content="Waiver Database: Revision: 0.0.1"/>

    <title>Open Access Waiver | Princeton University Library</title>
    <!-- Ajax Autocomplete Styling -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="//code.jquery.com/ui/1.11.2/themes/ui-lightness/jquery-ui.css">
    <!-- Bootstrap -->
    <link href="//maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.6/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <!-- PUL DSpace Theme -->
    <link href="//fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans:300,400,600,700" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">

    <link rel="stylesheet" media="all" href="/assets/application-ba907b143d10ecc12256155600195025ece363239ddf214db2249c0611d0b5d2.css" data-turbolinks-track="true" />
    <link rel="shortcut icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/assets/favicon-0e696af59f3106fd5cdbcf59b789dc678bf61e6c91c3a14db5af712ca706f9c6.ico" />
```
Using `lib-adc1`, I have identified that the incorrect IP address has been set for `oawaiver.princeton.edu`. I am manually correcting this now.

This should be fixed for the `lib-adc1` and `lib-adc2` load balancer nodes for NGINX Plus:

```bash
pulsys@lib-adc2:~$ curl https://oawaiver.princeton.edu
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <meta name="Generator" content="Waiver Database: Revision: 0.0.1"/>

    <title>Open Access Waiver | Princeton University Library</title>
```

This should be fixed for the `lib-adc1` and `lib-adc2` load balancer nodes for NGINX Plus:

```bash
pulsys@lib-adc2:~$ curl https://oawaiver.princeton.edu
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <meta name="Generator" content="Waiver Database: Revision: 0.0.1"/>

    <title>Open Access Waiver | Princeton University Library</title>
```

Following further investigation, I have discovered that `oawaiver-prod2` was indeed the desired host for deployment. Additionally, it was discovered that a locked dependency for `active-storage` needed to be resolved.
